          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function, which are computationally inexpensive. However, scalar functions in SQL Server can sometimes lead to performance issues when used in large queries or with large datasets due to their row-by-row execution nature. It is advisable to use this function judiciously in performance-critical applications."
